---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const publishDate = '2026-06-11';
const modifiedDate = '2026-06-11';
const author = 'David Hagon';
const readTime = '8 min read';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'When do Windows 10 security updates actually stop?',
    answer:
      "Mainstream Windows 10 support ended on 14 October 2025. If you enrolled in Microsoft's consumer Extended Security Updates (ESU) programme, you've been receiving security patches since then — but ESU is a one-year bridge, not a reprieve. It ends on 13 October 2026, and there is no consumer extension beyond that date. After it, a Windows 10 PC receives no security fixes at all.",
  },
  {
    question: "How do I check whether my PC is getting extended security updates?",
    answer:
      "Open Settings, go to Windows Update, and look for an 'Enrol now' link or confirmation that you're enrolled in Extended Security Updates. Also check Update History — if the most recent security update is from before October 2025 and you see no ESU enrolment, your PC has been unpatched for months. If you're not sure, bring it in and I'll check it as part of my £20 diagnostic, which is waived if you go ahead with any work.",
  },
  {
    question: "My PC says it can't run Windows 11 — do I have to buy a new computer?",
    answer:
      "Usually not. Many PCs that fail Microsoft's official checker only fail on TPM settings that can be enabled in the BIOS, and plenty of 'unsupported' machines with decent hardware can run Windows 11 cleanly with the right installation approach. If your PC runs Windows 10 well — especially if it has an SSD and 8GB+ RAM — there's a good chance it can be moved to Windows 11 for far less than the cost of a new machine.",
  },
  {
    question: 'Is it really dangerous to keep using Windows 10 after October 2026?',
    answer:
      "For anything connected to the internet, yes. Once patches stop, every newly discovered Windows 10 vulnerability stays open forever, and attackers deliberately target end-of-life systems because they know the holes will never be closed. Online banking, email, and shopping on an unpatched machine is a genuine risk — this is how ransomware and password-stealing infections get in. An offline machine used for nothing but, say, an old printer or hobby software is a different story.",
  },
  {
    question: 'How much does a Windows 11 upgrade cost at Chiltern Computers?',
    answer:
      "A Windows 11 installation including driver setup, updates, and basic configuration starts from £50, with data backup and restoration included. If your machine would benefit from an SSD or RAM upgrade at the same time — which makes a dramatic difference on older PCs — I'll quote that up front. The £20 diagnostic is waived if you proceed, and no fix, no fee applies.",
  },
  {
    question: 'Will my files and programs survive the move to Windows 11?',
    answer:
      "Your files, yes — always. I back up documents, photos, music, bookmarks, and email before any installation and restore them afterwards. An in-place upgrade from Windows 10 to 11 typically keeps your installed programs too. A clean install means reinstalling programs, but you get a faster, clutter-free system — I'll advise which route suits your machine.",
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Windows 10's Final Deadline: Security Updates End October 2026"
  description="Windows 10's extended security updates end for good on 13 October 2026. Upgrade to Windows 11, upgrade your hardware, or replace? Honest local advice from Romford."
  keywords="windows 10 end of support, windows 10 extended security updates end, windows 10 esu october 2026, windows 10 to windows 11 upgrade romford, windows 10 deadline 2026, what to do windows 10 end of life, windows 11 upgrade essex, windows 10 still safe 2026"
  image="/office-pc.webp"
  type="article"
  publishedTime={publishDate}
  modifiedTime={modifiedDate}
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Blog', url: '/blog/' },
    { name: "Windows 10's Final Deadline: Security Updates End October 2026", url: '/blog/windows-10-extended-security-updates-ending-2026/' },
  ]}
